<div   class="contextual-help-item principal-help"  i18n:domain="novaideo">
    <div tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="not request.is_idea_box" >
        <p i18n:translate="" tal:condition="not (request.support_ideas or request.support_proposals)">
            To write down an idea, access your content, or intervene on an idea or a proposal, you must beforehand be registered and connected.
        </p>
         <p i18n:translate="">
            If you are not connected, you will only be able to perform searches, to read content (ideas and proposals) and to see registered members.
        </p>
        <p i18n:translate="">
            An idea is a short, spontaneous personal note. A proposal is a complete, collectively written document, based on thorough work.
        </p>
        <p >
            <span i18n:translate="">An idea can either be archived, or "To be further worked upon",</span> 
            <span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="request.moderate_ideas">or submitted for moderation,</span> 
            <span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="not request.support_ideas">or published</span>
            <span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="request.examine_ideas">, or being examined</span> 
            <span i18n:translate="">A proposal can be in either one of the following states: private, open to a working group, under improvement, or the purpose of a vote to determine whether the proposal should be further improved or not,</span> 
            <span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="not request.support_proposals">or published</span>
            <span tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="request.support_proposals">or submitted for evaluation</span>
            <span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="'proposal' in request.content_to_examine">, or being examined</span>.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div  tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="request.is_idea_box">
        <p i18n:translate="">
            To write down an idea, access your content, or intervene on an idea or a proposal, you must beforehand be registered and connected.
        </p>
         <p i18n:translate="">
            If you are not connected, you will only be able to perform searches, to read content (ideas) and to see registered members.
        </p>
        <p i18n:translate="">
            An idea is a short, spontaneous, personal note.
        </p>
        <p >
            <span i18n:translate="">An idea can either be archived, or "To be further worked upon",</span> 
            <span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="request.moderate_ideas">or submitted for moderation,</span> 
            <span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="not request.support_ideas">or published</span>
            <span i18n:translate="" tal:omit-tag="" tal:condition="request.examine_ideas">, or being examined</span> 
            <span i18n:translate="">.
        </p>
    </div>
    <p i18n:translate="">
        With the advanced search and the filters, you can also refine your search, by specifying the time period, the type of content and its status, the keywords, the contributors and the texts to search.
    </p>
</div>
